DESCRIPTION
During etude-zcq, multiple review-gate seats (Opus verify + final) noted that internal/cli/sync.go fetch() at ~L142-143 maps fetchBangAbort to a generic error, but that switch case is provably DEAD: the preceding 'if classifyErr != nil { return classifyErr }' (~L136-137) always returns first whenever result is fetchBangAbort (the abort always carries a non-nil error). So the user already gets the richer classifyFetchBang error (now incl. merge-base stderr from etude-zcq). Cleanup: delete the dead case or have fetch() return classifyErr directly, to avoid misleading future readers. Behavior-preserving. Low priority.

